The paper discusses network representation learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and data mining that deals with embedding network vertices into a low-dimensional vector space. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including social and information networks (cs.SI), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), and statistical learning (cs.ST). However, given the focus on network analysis and representation, we believe that cs.SI is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.LG and cs.SD.
